    "id": "slide1",
    "eyebrow": "Introduction",
    "num": "01",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">01</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Introduction</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Why Change a Tire? Understanding the Need</h2><ul><li>Flat or damaged tires cause unsafe driving conditions</li><li>Changing a tire restores vehicle mobility and safety</li><li>Common causes: punctures, wear, or sudden damage</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Tire changes are essential when a tire is flat or damaged to maintain safe vehicle operation. Understanding why a tire needs changing helps prepare for the task and recognize urgency. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A nail punctures a tire on a road trip, causing a slow leak and eventual flat tire.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Think about what signs indicate your tire needs changing immediately.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring slow leaks or minor damage can lead to sudden tire failure.</p></div></div>",
    "paper": {
      "secnum": "Deep Dive 01",
      "h": "Common Causes of Tire Failure",
      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> Tire changes are essential when a tire is flat or damaged to maintain safe vehicle operation. Understanding why a tire needs changing helps prepare for the task and recognize urgency.</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from continental-tires.com; bobbyrahalhondaofstatecollege.com. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>Flat or damaged tires cause unsafe driving conditions</li><li>Changing a tire restores vehicle mobility and safety</li><li>Common causes: punctures, wear, or sudden damage</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>A nail punctures a tire on a road trip, causing a slow leak and eventual flat tire.</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Think about what signs indicate your tire needs changing immediately.</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Ignoring slow leaks or minor damage can lead to sudden tire failure.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> continental-tires.com; bobbyrahalhondaofstatecollege.com <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p>"
    },
    "poll": "poll1-reasons-tools"
