    "num": "05",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">05</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Spare Tire Limits</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Understanding Spare Tire Restrictions</h2><ul><li>Spare tires often have speed and distance limits</li><li>Temporary spares ('donuts') are smaller and less durable</li><li>Check spare tire pressure before use</li><li>Refer to vehicle manual for specific spare tire guidance</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Knowing the limitations of your spare tire helps avoid unsafe driving conditions after a tire change. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Driving no more than 50 mph and 70 miles on a donut spare as recommended.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Review your vehicle manual for spare tire restrictions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Driving long distances or at high speeds on a temporary spare can cause failure.</p></div></div>",
