    "eyebrow": "Hazard Recognition",
    "num": "06",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">06</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Hazard Recognition</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Identifying Hazards During a Tire Change</h2><ul><li>Traffic and passing vehicles pose risks</li><li>Unstable or uneven ground can cause jack failure</li><li>Slipping or pinching hazards during lifting and removal</li><li>Incorrect lifting points risk vehicle damage and injury</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Recognizing hazards helps prevent accidents and injuries during the tire change process. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Noticing a soft shoulder and choosing a firmer spot to place the jack.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> List potential hazards you might face changing a tire roadside.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring traffic risks or unstable ground can lead to serious accidents.</p></div></div>",
