    "id": "slide19",
    "eyebrow": "Post-Change Checks",
    "num": "19",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">19</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Post-Change Checks</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Perform Post-Change Safety Checks</h2><ul><li>Verify spare tire pressure and condition</li><li>Ensure all lug nuts are tight and secure</li><li>Store tools and removed tire properly</li><li>Check vehicle stability and brake function</li><li>Plan for professional tire repair or replacement</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Completing safety checks after changing the tire ensures the vehicle is safe to drive and that the spare tire is suitable for temporary use. Planning professional service addresses any unresolved issues. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Use a tire pressure gauge to check the spare tire pressure matches recommended levels before driving.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Create a checklist of post-change safety steps to follow after a tire change.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Failing to check spare tire pressure or lug nut tightness can lead to unsafe driving conditions.</p></div></div>",
