    "id": "slide20",
    "eyebrow": "When Not to Change a Tire Yourself",
    "num": "20",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">20</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>When Not to Change a Tire Yourself</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Recognize Situations Requiring Professional Help</h2><ul><li>Unsafe roadside conditions or heavy traffic</li><li>Lack of proper tools or vehicle-specific knowledge</li><li>Damaged or missing spare tire</li><li>Vehicle instability or jack failure</li><li>Physical inability or health concerns</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Knowing when not to attempt a tire change yourself helps prevent injury and further vehicle damage. Professional roadside assistance is safer in hazardous or complex situations. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> If your vehicle is on a busy highway shoulder with poor visibility, calling roadside assistance is safer than changing the tire yourself.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify scenarios where you would choose professional help over self-service.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Attempting a tire change in unsafe conditions can lead to accidents or injury.</p></div></div>",
