    "id": "slide21",
    "eyebrow": "Practice Checkpoint",
    "num": "21",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">21</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice Checkpoint</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Sequence the Tire Change Steps Correctly</h2><ul><li>Arrange these steps in the correct order:</li><li>1. Loosen lug nuts</li><li>2. Position and use the jack</li><li>3. Remove the damaged tire</li><li>4. Mount the spare tire</li><li>5. Tighten lug nuts in crisscross pattern</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Understanding the correct sequence ensures safety and efficiency during a tire change. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s17\">[17]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The correct order starts with loosening lug nuts before lifting, then lifting the vehicle, and so on.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write down the steps in the correct order and explain why each step follows the previous one.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Skipping or rearranging steps can cause safety hazards or damage.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide21\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;What is the correct pattern to tighten wheel fasteners after mounting the spare tire?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;Crisscross or star pattern&quot;,&quot;Clockwise in a circle&quot;,&quot;Counterclockwise in a circle&quot;,&quot;Random order&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;Tightening lug nuts in a crisscross or star pattern ensures even pressure and proper wheel seating, preventing damage or loosening.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Describe the key safety checks you must perform before starting to change a tire.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Answer should include stopping in a safe location, setting parking brake, placing warning devices, checking vehicle stability, and using personal protective measures.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Before changing a tire, I would stop the vehicle in a safe and visible area, apply the parking brake, place warning triangles or cones, ensure the ground is stable and level, and wear gloves and reflective clothing if available.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;stop in safe location&quot;,&quot;apply parking brake&quot;,&quot;set warning devices&quot;,&quot;check vehicle stability&quot;,&quot;use personal safety measures&quot;,&quot;wear gloves&quot;,&quot;wear reflective clothing&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
    "paper": {
      "secnum": "Deep Dive 21",
      "h": "Why Following the Correct Sequence Matters",
      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> Understanding the correct sequence ensures safety and efficiency during a tire change.</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from bobbyrahalhondaofstatecollege.com; federalregister.gov. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>Arrange these steps in the correct order:</li><li>1. Loosen lug nuts</li><li>2. Position and use the jack</li><li>3. Remove the damaged tire</li><li>4. Mount the spare tire</li><li>5. Tighten lug nuts in crisscross pattern</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>The correct order starts with loosening lug nuts before lifting, then lifting the vehicle, and so on.</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Write down the steps in the correct order and explain why each step follows the previous one.</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Skipping or rearranging steps can cause safety hazards or damage.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> bobbyrahalhondaofstatecollege.com; federalregister.gov <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s17\">[17]</sup></p>"
    }
