    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">22</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Hazard Identification Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Identify Hazards in a Tire Change Scenario</h2><ul><li>Review a roadside tire change setup</li><li>Spot potential hazards like traffic, ground instability, or poor visibility</li><li>Suggest safety measures to mitigate each hazard</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Practicing hazard identification prepares learners to set up a safer work environment during tire changes. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Noticing that the vehicle is parked on a slope and suggesting wheel chocks to prevent rolling.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> List hazards you observe in a given tire change photo or description and propose safety actions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking hazards can lead to accidents or ineffective safety measures.</p></div></div>",
