    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">24</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Safety Decision Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Decide When to Call for Professional Help</h2><ul><li>Evaluate scenarios for safety and capability</li><li>Consider environmental, vehicle, and personal factors</li><li>Choose self-service or professional assistance accordingly</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Practicing decision-making helps learners recognize when a tire change is unsafe or impractical to perform alone. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> In heavy rain on a busy highway, calling roadside assistance is safer than changing the tire yourself.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Review different scenarios and decide whether to change the tire yourself or seek professional help, explaining your reasoning.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Underestimating hazards or overestimating ability can lead to dangerous situations.</p></div></div>",
